WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:11.120
Hi, I am Pamela Pairo, Ph.D., Biological Sciences from Argentina. In this presentation, I am

00:00:11.120 --> 00:00:16.920
going to show you how to create a multilingual website using blogdown, YouGo, and Netlify.

00:00:16.920 --> 00:00:22.080
First of all, why do you need a personal website? Having a personal website is another way to

00:00:22.080 --> 00:00:27.840
showcase your CV or resume with styles and gives you the freedom to be creative. By writing

00:00:27.840 --> 00:00:33.759
posts, you will practice your communication skills, you can exchange knowledge with colleagues,

00:00:33.759 --> 00:00:38.520
and therefore, your networking will be expanded. In my experience, when I came across with

00:00:38.520 --> 00:00:44.400
difficulties or doubts, I had able to solve the issues thanks to the posts shared by others.

00:00:44.400 --> 00:00:50.840
And finally, the personal website is a platform to connect with the world. For those of us

00:00:50.840 --> 00:00:55.560
who aren't native English speakers, it is fundamental to have a multilingual website

00:00:55.560 --> 00:01:01.400
in English to disseminate our work to the global community and in our native language

00:01:01.400 --> 00:01:07.959
to make our website content more inclusive and accessible for everyone. Let's get started.

00:01:07.959 --> 00:01:15.360
We begin creating a new repo in our GitHub account. Then, in RStudio, create a new project

00:01:15.360 --> 00:01:20.680
with Contribution, Undownload, Blogdown, and YouGo. You can look at all the themes and

00:01:20.680 --> 00:01:27.599
select one on the YouGo website. After that, you will have the default version of the site

00:01:27.599 --> 00:01:33.519
in the viewer panel, so it's time to customize. The main files that are part of the website

00:01:33.519 --> 00:01:39.120
are shown here. In config.tom is where it's located the global settings for the site and

00:01:39.120 --> 00:01:46.760
in config.default folder are the params.toms where you can change the color theme, the

00:01:46.760 --> 00:01:54.599
font size of your website, and add your contact details. To change what appears in the navigation

00:01:54.599 --> 00:01:59.919
menu bar, it's necessary to edit the menu.tom file. And in language.tom is where you can

00:01:59.919 --> 00:02:06.839
change the language setting. And how to make your personal website multilingual? I'm going

00:02:06.839 --> 00:02:14.839
to show you an example of the bilingual website, English and Spanish. In the language.tom,

00:02:14.839 --> 00:02:21.839
you have to uncomment the lines for a second language to configure your website. Here we

00:02:21.839 --> 00:02:27.399
have the information about the English part, for example, the language code, where it's

00:02:27.399 --> 00:02:33.919
located the content, and the title. Note that the abbreviations of the languages are predefined,

00:02:33.919 --> 00:02:40.720
so if you want a Portuguese website, for example, you need to check which is the correct abbreviation.

00:02:40.720 --> 00:02:49.839
Then, in each language, we'll need their own menu.tom file and a subfolder within the content

00:02:49.839 --> 00:02:57.520
folder. Finally, choose the default language that the visitors will see when visit your page,

00:02:57.520 --> 00:03:04.360
and for making visible that the website is multilingual, check in params.tom that show

00:03:04.839 --> 00:03:11.520
is true. When you are done with your edits and you are happy with your website, it's time to

00:03:11.520 --> 00:03:18.320
put it online. One way to do this is using Netlify. One of the advantages of deploying

00:03:18.320 --> 00:03:24.559
your website through Netlify is that it allows you to have a static site for free and easily.

00:03:24.559 --> 00:03:30.759
Basically, it connects to the remote repository on GitHub to deploy. Every change that it makes

00:03:30.960 --> 00:03:41.160
on the website, it will be automatically updated after to push to GitHub. It's important that the

00:03:41.160 --> 00:03:49.600
Hugo version that you are running locally match with the version that Netlify is going to use to

00:03:49.600 --> 00:03:58.720
build your site, and how to do that? Check your local version of Hugo and pick up the Netlify

00:03:58.720 --> 00:04:08.320
file to your project root directory and specify the Hugo version. Then, go to the Netlify webpage

00:04:08.320 --> 00:04:17.920
and log in with GitHub to select the repo you've been working with lockdown. You will see something

00:04:17.920 --> 00:04:25.000
like this but with your information. Go to show advanced and just in case, write the Hugo version,

00:04:25.079 --> 00:04:32.760
and finally, you will have your website. In the latest version of lockdown, you can set up the

00:04:32.760 --> 00:04:39.880
Hugo version by running this code and tell to Netlify the Hugo version with this function.

00:04:39.880 --> 00:04:47.559
If you want more information, here are some blogs that I used in this presentation and

00:04:47.559 --> 00:04:52.920
you can find me on my website and on Twitter. Thank you.

